4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Existing state statute enacted by the
6 Legislature in 2023 recognizes the fundamental rights
7 of parents to direct the education, upbringing, care,
8 and control of their children and references the
9 recognition of those parental rights by the Alabama
10 Supreme Court and the United States Supreme Court.
11 This bill would propose an amendment to the
12 Constitution of Alabama of 2022, to provide that: (i)
13 parents have a fundamental right to direct the
14 education, upbringing, care, custody, and control of
15 their children; and (ii) the government may not burden
16 that right unless the government demonstrates that the
17 burden as applied to the parent is in furtherance of a
18 compelling government interest and the government uses
19 the least restrictive means possible to further that
20 interest.
21
22
23 A BILL
24 TO BE ENTITLED
25 AN ACT
26
27 Proposing an amendment to the Constitution of Alabama
28 of 2022, to provide that parents have a fundamental right to
