of 2022, to provide that parents have a fundamental right to
HB148 INTRODUCED
29 direct the education, upbringing, care, custody, and control
30 of their children; and to provide that the government may not
31 burden certain fundamental rights of parents.
32 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
33 Section 1. The following amendment to the Constitution
34 of Alabama of 2022, is proposed:
35 PROPOSED AMENDMENT
36 (a) Each parent has the fundamental right to direct the
37 education, upbringing, care, custody, and control of his or
38 her child.
39 (b) The government may not burden the fundamental right
40 of a parent to direct the education, upbringing, care,
41 custody, and control of his or her child unless the government
42 demonstrates that the application of the burden as applied to
43 the parent is in furtherance of a compelling governmental
44 interest and the government uses the least restrictive means
45 possible to further that interest.
46 Upon ratification of this constitutional amendment, the
47 Code Commissioner shall number and place this amendment as
48 appropriate in the constitution omitting this instructional
49 paragraph and may make the following nonsubstantive revisions:
50 change capitalization, hierarchy, spelling, and punctuation
51 for purposes of style and uniformity; correct manifest
52 grammatical, clerical, and typographical errors; revise
53 internal or external citations and cross-references; harmonize
54 language; and translate effective dates.
55 END OF PROPOSED AMENDMENT
56 Section 2. An election upon the proposed amendment
