Section 2. An election upon the proposed amendment
HB148 INTRODUCED
57 shall be held in accordance with Sections 284 and 285 of the
58 Constitution of Alabama of 2022, and the election laws of this
59 state. The appropriate election official shall assign a ballot
60 number for the proposed constitutional amendment on the
61 election ballot and shall set forth the following description
62 of the substance or subject matter of the proposed
63 constitutional amendment:
64 "Proposing an amendment to the Constitution of Alabama
65 of 2022, to provide that each parent has a fundamental right
66 to direct the education, upbringing, care, custody, and
67 control of his or her children, and that the government may
68 not burden that fundamental right unless the government
69 demonstrates that the application of the burden as applied to
70 the parent is in furtherance of a compelling governmental
71 interest and uses the least restrictive means possible to
72 further that interest.
73 Proposed by Act ____."
74 This description shall be followed by the following
75 language:
76 "Yes( ) No( )."
77 Section 3. The proposed amendment shall become valid as
78 a part of the Constitution of Alabama of 2022, when approved
79 by a majority of the qualified electors voting thereon.
